Sort an array in ascending order using the algorithm known as Quicksort. The algorithm has a time complexity of O(nlog(n)) and a space complexity of O(1), making it an efficient and optimal solution to the problem. Implementing with C++.
```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

void quicksort(int nums[], int low, int high) {
    // If the partition is already done, just return the sorted array.
    if (low < high) {
        int p = partition(nums, low, high);
        quicksort(nums, low, p - 1);
        quicksort(nums, p + 1, high);
    }
}

